Document: VisualShaderNodeClamp
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernodeclamp.rst
Summary: Clamps a value within the visual shader graph to ensure it stays within specified bounds.

Inherits: VisualShaderNode < Resource < RefCounted < Object
Clamps a value within the visual shader graph. This node restricts the output of a shader value to a defined range, preventing it from exceeding minimum or maximum thresholds. The clamping operation ensures that any input value is constrained between the specified lower and upper bounds, which is useful for controlling color intensity, texture coordinates, or other shader parameters that require range limitations.
